<br>
<br>
I'm not sure of the exact figures now, but I think these are close:  assume about 1500 cases and about 80 deaths.. That's 5% mortality rate.<br>
<br>
Now add in those who contracted the disease but never got ill enough to seek hospitalization or, perhaps, even display symptoms..perhaps as much as double those who did.  That drops the mortality rate to 1-2%..<br>
<br>
The 1918-19 epidemic had a mortality rate around 30%..<br>
<br>
Malaria and tuberculosis combine to kill almost 6 million people, per annum..<br>
<br>
