lign=absmiddle>  Re: Sars</span><hr size=1> The 1918 flu infected nearly a billion people and killed over 20 million. The really surprising thing about it is that, unlike *Normal* flu, it was most lethel for young people, In some areas teens and early twentys did indeed suffer up to 30% fatalitys! This is from the same generation that had already suffererd heavy casualties from the war. that is what made this plague so devestating.<br>
